description: For sale: $850,000. A stunning and unique property located 10 miles from downtown St. Paul and less than 3 miles from the Minnesota Vikings Training Center in Eagan.  This 5 acre property offers mature trees, incredible privacy, and multiple options on land use for the buyer.   This is a rare opportunity to purchase a large lot close to a metropolitan area.   The property has a custom-built home with 5 bedrooms, 2 baths and a 2 car garage that was built in 1987.   On the property is also a separate heated shop that can accommodate 2 vehicles.  The home and shop sit on 2 of the 5 acres.   Potential for redevelopment now or in the future.   Excellent building sites on property for new home(s).   Property is also zoned by City of Inver Grove Heights for multi-family housing - opportunity for redevelopment of over 50 units.   Distinctive property with a great deal of options based on buyer's interest and vision.    Lots of options with this property!   Worth a look!

description:
For sale: $399,900. Hard to find acreage property at a great price near the cities! This hidden treasure is nestled on 3.82 acres & is surrounded by woods and open space for room to roam. Enjoy the beautiful nature, & privacy, 
while still being in a convenient location. Located in the 196 school district. This home offers 3 bedrooms on one level, private master bathroom, gorgeous hardwood flooring, gas fireplace, wet bar, attached 3 car garage, detached 1 car garage, large deck overlooking the woods, newer appliances including dual fuel range, newer roof, and much more!

For sale: $1,195,000. Masterpiece walk-out rambler on acreage and a pond exudes quality craftsmanship, one-of-a-kind details and elegance. This architect-designed home enjoys a layout that is both easy for everyday living and ideal for entertaining. Appreciate the remarkable woodwork and design elements throughout, family-style kitchen, impressive owner's suite, main level mother-in law suite, in ground pool, and a lower level entertaining wet bar/billiard area. So many luxurious things its a must have!!

For sale: $797,000. Enjoy 5.38 Private Acres, Rambler with 2,598 Finished Sq Ft, 40x60 shop with 14 ft ceilings, 2 - 12x12 garage doors, floor drain, heated 2x6 wall construction, 200 amp service, private bath and much more- please see supplements. All 1 level living, beautiful screened in porch with deck/stairs. 3 bedrooms, 4 baths, all rooms are over-sized in this custom built home, master bedroom with ensuite bathroom. Must see to appreciate the value and opportunity!

Original Owners, Meticulously  Maintained.  Many Features.  OPEN FLOOR PLAN on Main level.  Cherry cabinets, granite counter throughout, 2 gas fireplaces, (one see-thru) hardwood floors in Kitchen and Dining Areas, and ceramic on lower level Bar/Walkout. Humidifier, water filtration system, Pool/Pond - Natural water with skimmer, Fire-Pit w/Stamped Concrete 15' x 15' and 20' x 25' Patio.  2.54 acres w/wildlife.  15-zone irrigation w/well. description: Recently sold: $362,000. Move-in ready St. Croix floor plan (3 bedroom, 2.5 bath) with many great upgrades! Dark Maple cabinets with soft close drawers, granite countertops with a huge center island/breakfast bar, laminate woods floors on the whole main level, cozy gas fireplace, big 8x15 deck off the kitchen. Never a punch hole in the walls. French doors leading into the spacious master bedroom with a private owner's bathroom and huge walk-in closet. Beautiful view over the pond and woods. Walkout basement roughed in and ready to be finished. Would add another bedroom and bathroom once complete. Less then three year old washer/dryer and stainless steel appliances. In highly sought after 196 school district.

Recently sold: $355,000. This home lives and feels brand new.   Situated on a premium, tree lined lot with windows across the back offering tons of natural light.  Beautiful on trend colors, finishes and upgrades. Luxury laminate plank flooring on main level, granite island & countertops throughout, as well as, soft close cabinets, ss appliances, upper level laundry, dual vanities in both upper baths, oversized maintenance free deck/railing.  The open floor plan is sensible for both everyday living and entertaining. School district 196 - Eagan Schools, convenient location and easy access to multiple freeways.

Recently sold: $518,000. Take a Virtual Tour of the Bristol floorplan! Welcome to Lennar's Bristol floorplan. The Bristol offers homeowners 2,185 square feet to 2,905 square feet of living space and is a apart of our Traditional Collection. This two-story home has an open concept floorplan - perfect for gathering with family and friends. The main level of the Bristol has a kitchen with a center island and walk-in pantry that overlooks the dining room and family room. A beautiful foyer, flex room, mudroom, and powder room are also included on the main level of this floorplan. An owner's suite plus an additional three bedrooms can be found on the upper level of the Bristol. The owner's suite features a large walk-in closet and a private bathroom with a separate shower and soaking tub and a double sink vanity. A full bathroom and a laundry room are also on the upper level of the Bristol.

Recently sold: $475,000. Gorgeous, one owner two story home on a private wooded half acre lot! Updated kitchen with custom cabinetry, stainless steel appliances, and granite counter-tops. Large family room with gas fireplace and custom built-ins. Screened in 3 season porch and large deck overlook extensive backyard. Large master suite includes double sink vanity, private bath, and a walk-in closet. Walk out basement leads out to the patio.

Recently sold: $564,960. Take a Virtual Tour of the McKinley floorplan! Welcome to Lennar's McKinley floorplan! The floorplan of the McKinley is as charming as it is spacious, ranging from 2,786 square feet to 3,876 square feet of living space. A part of our Traditional Collection, the McKinley's kitchen has a large island, walk-in pantry, and dinette area that overlooks the family room. The kitchen flows into the adjacent formal dining room located off the foyer. A private study, mudroom, and powder room complete the main level. On the upper level of the McKinley, you will find three bedrooms, an owner's suite, a full bathroom, and a conveniently located laundry room. The owner's suite has a beautiful private bathroom and two walk-in closets.

description: Recently sold: $324,900. Nearly renovated to perfection with numerous expensive upgrades! Huge walkout rambler featuring 4 bedrooms on the main level, main floor mud room with wainscoting. Located in a cul-de-sac, steps away from Groveland Park. Beautifully updated kitchen with attractive white cabinets, granite countertops, huge center island with a breakfast bar area, attractive pendent lighting, hardwood flooring, sliding glass door that leads to a newer maintenance free deck with attractive newel posts. Living room has gorgeous hardwood floors, enameled painted trim, double sided fireplace, white panel doors. Updated guest and master bathrooms, real tile. Master suite, walk in closet, formal dining with hardwood floors. 1/2 bath on main. Lower level walkout. Some of the other updates include furnace & air conditioning, water heater, partial fence, roof, garage doors with windows, driveway, some of the windows, lower level flooring and painting.

Recently sold: $475,000. Stunning home! Upon entering, you will value the intentional space of the entryway which makes receiving guests a pleasure! The living room boasts built-ins for curling up with a good book, and a double-sided custom fireplace to keep you warm in winter! The kitchen shines with beautiful cabinetry, striking granite counters, and stainless-steel appliances! Make memories, sharing a meal together with family and friends in the Dining Room! Off the Kitchen, you will find a mudroom, powder room, and office! Just a step outside the dining space is a great deck overlooking the beautifully landscaped yard. Upstairs holds all three bedrooms and laundry! The Master includes serene views and a spacious Master Bath!Build equity not only with an unfinished basement but an unfinished bonus room as well! An additional living space is roughed in above the garage and awaits your finishing! The neighborhood has walking trails, parks, a friendly community and is close to shopping, and restaurants.

description:
Recently sold: $469,000. Welcome to this custom/quality built home for sale in Inver Grove Heights MN with four bedrooms, four bathrooms and a premium 0.28 acre lot! Enjoy over 3,960 finished square feet of spacious elegance! The inviting entryway leads you into the home w/gorgeous maple hardwood floors! Relax/entertain in the massive living room w/vaulted ceilings, gas fireplace w/floor-to-ceiling stone surround and expansive picture windows that fill the room with natural light! The gourmet kitchen features beautiful maple cabinets, stainless steel appliances, gas range w/dual ovens, granite countertops, tiled backsplash and a breakfast bar--great for extra seating! The adjoining dining room has a walkout to the deck that overlooks a premium lot! The main level master suite boasts coved ceilings, a walk-in closet w/built-in organizers and a full bathroom with dual sinks, jetted tub and a separate shower! In addition, the main level has fantastic office space--work from home, laundry and a half bathroom! The upper level features a spacious loft that overlooks the living room, unique niche for displaying your possessions, two good sized bedrooms--one with vaulted ceilings and a full bathroom! The finished/walkout lower level includes a spacious family room w/gas fireplace w/stone surround, wired for surround sound and a wet bar w/recreation space, built-in shelving, 4th bedroom and another full bathroom! description:
Recently sold: $285,377. Private & Peaceful setting on a one of a kind lot. Well cared for throughout the years!

3 Bedroom, 2 bath home, situated on a 2.67 acre lot in ISD 196. Beautiful setting, with lots of walnut trees!

Two car garage attached, plus a new (2012) two car detached garage.Perfect for toys, or working on vehicles!

Nice paver patio along with frontporch. A touch of moss adds a comfortable patina.

Great living room, with a huge picture window overlooking the deck and wooded backyard. Ceiling beams add visual interest to the large room. New carpet in 2010. Living room also has a brickwood-burning fireplace, adding coziness for those cold days.

The dining room also has a huge window. One wall adds a lot of storage to thekitchen area, including a pantry cupboard and a bill-paying desk.

Galley kitchen was updated in 2002, with new countertops, sink, flooring, and refrigerator. A new dishwasher was added in approx. 2009, and a new range/oven in 2015.

The master bedroom has two windows, and two closets (his-and-hers). Beautiful hardwood floors in all three bedrooms.

Main level full bathroom has double sinks, and a daylight window. Everything, including the tub and tile, are in great shape! Added bonus of a huge linen closet in thebath. This home has quite a bit of storage space!

The lower level family room has newer carpet (2012). it is a spacious room, with recessed lighting. A 3/4 bath is right off the family room. The bath was updated in 2012, with new flooring, shower door, vanity and sink.

The laundry room features a large counter/cupboard and sink area, with a smaller cabinet/counter on the opposite wall. Both ends of the room off extra storage rooms, including one with built-in storage shelving.

There is another large, unfinished room on the lower level. This one is set up as a shop.

Spacious two-level deck overlooks the vast back yard.There is also a cute little playhouse on theproperty, and a storage shed. Beautiful yard, with mature trees adding lots of shade. Much privacy offered here!

Extensive updates over theyears include: New well pump, 2000; furnace/boiler, 2005; water softener, 2008; roof & gutters, 2009; insulated garage door plus opener, 2009; A/C, 2013; upgraded electrical panel, 2015.

Directions 70th street, 1 block west of Robert St. (Hwy 3).

description: Recently sold: $405,000. Original owner that has given home loving care. 2.7 acre wooded lot with privacy and abundance of trees. Newer roof and furnace. In-ground 16x32 pool for summer relaxation. Gas Fireplace in Family Room and rough-in for fireplace in Living Room. Great Home in super convenient neighborhood.
Recently sold: $123,000.

Recently sold: $710,000. Walk out rambler with open floor plan, chef's kitchen, 3 large bedrooms, 4 bathrooms, music room, living room, large theater family room with huge bar for entertaining, office, locker room with separate washer & dryer, outside entrance for oversized pool (20x45 feet & 9 ½ feet deep for diving board) and 8 person hot tub.  Entire house (including back yard) is wired for home audio connected to one remote, security system and DirecTV.  Security camera system installed with live viewing from computer or phone with 2 week playback.
Four car heated garage with finished walls and lots of cabinets for storage.  Fourth stall is currently set up as a workshop and has loft for even more storage.  Hot and Cold water faucet in garage with drain for winter car washes indoors or even pet baths.
Main Floor: Large open entry with vaulted ceilings, music room that could be used as a dining room, and family room.  Brazilian cherry wood floors throughout main level with the exception of piano room, tile bathrooms & mud room and guest bedroom.  Wood floors refinished September 2016.
Kitchen has 60" Wolf stove (6 burners, grill, griddle & 2 convection ovens) complete with vent & makeup air system.  Stainless GE Monogram appliances; subzero oversized refrigerator, microwave/warming oven/convection oven combo, dishwasher & wine fridge, center island with prep sink and bar seating and granite counter tops.  Walk in pantry and tons of cabinets for storage.  
Master bedroom with wood floors, 2 walk in closets & large master bath with double sinks, granite counters, walk in ceramic tile double shower and separate double jet tub with ceramic tile surround.
Office with door to deck and lots of windows overlooking back yard & wood floors.  Could be used as extra guest room too.
Full guest bathroom, a 2nd bedroom and mudroom finish out the first floor.
Lower Level has 1BR that is a smaller version of the master bedroom & bath, with 1 walk in closet and a separate study room.  Double sinks in bath with lots of cabinets and oversized shower.  Large oversized window for lots of natural light.
Large bar with ice maker, beverage fridge, oversized sink, dishwasher and microwave/convection/warming oven combo.  Granite counters and tile floor.  Bar can seat 8-12 people depending on size of bar stools.
Large entertainment space with 8ft projection TV screen that is stored in ceiling, great for movies or the big game.  Open space big enough for pool table, ping pong table or more seating. 
¾ bath with walk through to locker room and outside entrance (no wet bodies on your carpet coming in from the pool or hot tub).  Locker room with lockers for guest storage, space for storing all your pool toys in the off season, seprate washer and dryer for all the towels and teenager?s laundry living downstairs. 
Plenty of storage space in this home with a small carpteted storage area off the locker room, under stairway finished, carpeted storage with locked door and huge storage room downstairs complete the home.
Extras:  most door knobs, cabinet pulls, bathroom light fixtures and other bathroom hardware are from Pottery Barn or Restoration Hardware.  Recessed lighting throughout home with many switches on dimmers.  Lots of outdoor outlets, including one on roof for lights.  3 outdoor water faucets for hoses; garage (with hot & cold water), on side of house and backyard. Fenced back yard.   Invisible fence around entire property. New roof 2014.
Pool has electric safety cover (open & close with a light switch), new in 2012 and motor will be replaced in spring 2017 with pool opening.  New pool pump motor in 2012.  New in floor vacuum system & diving board in 2016.  Pool and all equipment serviced by Valley Pools in Burnsville.
Master bedroom & lower level bedroom have TV hookups for large wall TVs. Sound proof insulation in floor/ceiling of master BR and lower level BR - blocks tv, music, friends over and late night talking on the phone!

Many updates since I bought 3 years ago, including new lighting and fans throughout, new neutral paint, bathroom upgrades including new sink, counter, faucet and lighting, kitchen upgrades include new appliances and lighting including under cabinet lighting, new counter, sink, faucet and garbage disposal. Close to shopping, 52/494, and many parks and trails.

Owner pays HOA fees. Association pays water and garbage. Heat/electric, cable are the responsibility of renter.
